chapters.text:
they deserve no good at his hands, but the very reverse. "Wherefore does a
living man complain, a man for the punishment of his sins?" Lamentations 3:39;
Psalm 103:10.

intelligible to us. The Lord has a "therefore" in answer to every "wherefore";
but he does not often reveal it; for "he gives not account of any of his
matters": Job 33:13.
